Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.52,0:00:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Essential Hayek \N 欢迎来到哈耶克简要
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.56,0:00:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Don Boudreaux \N 我是Don Boudreaux
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.14,0:00:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,professor of economics at George Mason University \N 乔治梅森大学经济学教授
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.04,0:00:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,senior fellow with the Fraser Institute \N 弗雷泽研究所高级研究员
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.14,0:00:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and blogger at Café Hayek \N 博客Café Hayek的博主之一
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.31,0:00:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This video was part of the Fraser Institute initiative \N 本视频是由弗雷泽研究所制作的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.10,0:00:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to present the key ideas of F.A. Hayek in an easily accessible format \N 对哈耶克关键思想的通俗介绍
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.28,0:00:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In this video, we explore Hayek's work on economic booms and busts \N 本视频将介绍哈耶克对经济繁荣和衰退的研究
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.44,0:00:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,work for which he was awarded a Nobel prize in economics in 1974 \N 哈耶克因此研究获得了1974年诺贝尔经济学奖
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.96,0:00:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One of Hayek's key observations was that when government interfering the economy \N 哈耶克的一个关键发现是政府对经济的干预
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.38,0:00:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it results in people acting in ways that are not sustainable \N 会导致人们以不可持续的方式行动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.08,0:00:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which ultimately leads to booms and then, inevitably, busts \N 这将产生经济的短期繁荣和之后不可避免的萧条
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.80,0:00:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's simplify this idea with an example \N 让我们举个栗子来简化下这个想法
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.44,0:00:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Brian \N 这是Brian
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.44,0:00:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Brian is a politician who thinks he has a great idea for creating jobs and widespread prosperity \N 他觉得自己有了一个能制造就业并创造广泛繁荣的好想法
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.68,0:01:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,With the best intentions \N 怀着最大的好意
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.38,0:01:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Brian convinces his government to support companies \N Brian说服政府支持企业
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.32,0:01:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they can develop and build factories to sell chocolate-covered pickles \N 以让它们建造生产巧克力裹酸黄瓜的工厂
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.82,0:01:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but Brian's plan is flawed \N 但是Brian的计划是有缺陷的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.30,0:01:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he assumes there will be great demand for chocolate-covered pickles \N 他以为对巧克力裹酸黄瓜的需求将会很大
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.64,0:01:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but if they're truly with great demand for chocolate-covered pickles \N 但假如真有大量的需求
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.48,0:01:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the pickle industry will naturally respond \N 酸黄瓜制造业自然会做出反应
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.72,0:01:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and build factories of covered pickles with chocolate \N 去建设巧克力裹酸黄瓜工厂
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.86,0:01:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All without the government assistance \N 这一切都无需政府帮助
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.88,0:01:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so what happens when there is no real demand by customers for chocolate-covered pickles \N 所以假如消费者其实并不需要巧克力裹酸黄瓜，那将会怎样？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.86,0:01:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the resources provided by the government \N 那样的话，政府提供的资源
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.00,0:01:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,whether in the form of direct support like subsidies \N 如直接的经济补贴
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.54,0:01:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or indirect support like loan guarantees \N 或间接的贷款担保
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.88,0:01:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,distorts the economy by encouraging people to make bad decisions \N 都会诱使人们做出错误的决策从而扭曲经济
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.44,0:01:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case \N 在这个例子中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.88,0:01:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to use resources to make chocolate-covered pickles \N 错误决策指的就是调用资源去生产无人需要的巧克力裹酸黄瓜
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.00,0:01:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As the lack of demand for these pickles becomes apparent \N 当人们意识到对巧克力裹酸黄瓜的需求其实并不存在时
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,businesses must adjust by retooling \N 企业就必须重组
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.32,0:01:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or even scuttling factories \N 甚至关闭工厂
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.08,0:01:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,adjusting their production lines \N 调整生产线
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.08,0:02:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,changing their distribution networks, et cetera \N 改变分销渠道等等
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.84,0:02:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these things mean idle resources in the short term \N 这些都意味着在经济体自我调整以适应市场的这段时期
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.94,0:02:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as businesses adjust to the reality of the market \N 会产生资源的短期闲置
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.66,0:02:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The challenge is to ensure that producers \N 经济正确运行的难处就在于如何让生产者
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.94,0:02:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,have the knowledge and the incentives to \N 获得正确的信息和激励
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.34,0:02:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,produce goods and services that people want \N 去生产人们需要的产品和服务
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Government interference, such as through subsidies \N 政府干预，例如补贴
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.02,0:02:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or specially importantly, by manipulating the money supply \N 或者影响更大的货币供应调节
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.86,0:02:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,obscure that knowledge by distorting prices \N 扭曲了价格从而模糊了传递给生产者的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.28,0:02:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This interference \N 这种政府干预
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.60,0:02:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by initially causing producers to tool up \N 先会导致厂家升级设备
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.72,0:02:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to produce things that consumers don't really want \N 去生产消费者其实并不需要的产品
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.28,0:02:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,inevitably results in producers having to tool down and readjust \N 然后不可避免地废弃设备、重新调整
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.16,0:02:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to better meet true consumer demands \N 以适应消费者的真实需求
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.24,0:02:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The core insight from Hayek on economic booms and busts \N 哈耶克对于经济周期的核心观点在于
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.52,0:02:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is that government interference, even when done with the best intentions \N 即使是抱有最大好意的政府干预
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.76,0:02:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,changes people's behavior by changing incentives and changing signals in the market \N 也会因为改变了市场上的激励和信号而改变人们的行为
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.99,0:02:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,These changes result in investments that are not sustainable \N 这些改变会导致不可持续的投资
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.28,0:03:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and which automatically leads to recessions, or busts \N 进而导致经济衰退
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.22,0:03:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn more and to download <Essential Hayek> for free \N 想要下载和更多了解《哈耶克简要》
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.36,0:03:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,visit www.essentialhayek.org \N 请访问www.essentialhayek.org
